@startuml http_request_response
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title HTTP Request-Response Cycle

actor Client as C
participant "DNS\nServer" as DNS
participant "Web\nServer" as WS
database "Data\nStore" as DB

C -> DNS : Resolve api.example.com
DNS --> C : IP: 203.0.113.42

C -> WS : **HTTP Request**\nGET /api/works/123\nHost: api.example.com\nAccept: application/json\nAuthorization: Bearer token

activate WS
WS -> WS : Authenticate request
WS -> WS : Validate parameters
WS -> DB : Query data
activate DB
DB --> WS : Result set
deactivate DB
WS -> WS : Serialize to JSON
WS --> C : **HTTP Response**\n200 OK\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{"id": 123, "title": "..."}
deactivate WS

note right of C
  **Request Components**
  • Method (GET, POST, etc.)
  • Path (/api/works/123)
  • Headers (Auth, Accept)
  • Body (for POST/PUT)
end note

note left of WS
  **Response Components**
  • Status Code (200, 404, etc.)
  • Headers (Content-Type)
  • Body (JSON data)
end note

@enduml
